snippet: Democrats say that the law’s woes are cutting into the momentum they gained after the government shutdown, and that the troubles could cost them in the 2014 midterm races.
abstract: Pres Obama is facing broad and mounting Democratic concerns that troubled start of health care insurance program will cut into political benefit the party received from government shutdown and could cost them in 2014 midterm races; many anxious Democrats say the Obama administration must extend period to enroll in new plans, given the continuing problems with Web site access.
lead_paragraph: Democrats say that the law’s woes are cutting into the momentum they gained after the government shutdown, and that the troubles could cost them in the 2014 midterm races.

headline.main: Troubled Start for Health Law Has Democrats Feeling Anxious
